name: acc. manage
format: 👥 User Management

label: This dummy system simulates the operation of an AC motor integrated with an Omron PLC, Weintek HMI, and IIoT capabilities using MQTT and Node-RED. The Weintek HMI acts as the user interface, allowing the operator to initialize the system, acknowledge safety checks, and start or stop the motor. When the motor is started, the PLC energizes a contactor or VFD to power the motor, while also monitoring parameters such as temperature, vibration, and power consumption. These readings are mapped to PLC registers (e.g., D300–D302) and used for real-time condition checks. If thresholds are exceeded, warning flags are set (e.g., M210 for over-temperature), and the HMI displays alert messages accordingly. The motor's operational state is stored in registers (e.g., D100 = 1 for running) and reset when stopped via the HMI.  In parallel, the system transmits real-time data to a Node-RED dashboard using MQTT.
